      "t": "p",
      "x": "MECHANISM 3 — VMAT DISPLACEMENT (tyramine). Tyramine is taken into the neuron, loaded into vesicles by VMAT, and displaces vesicular NE, which then leaves via reversal of NET. It overlaps the amphetamine mechanism but is worth its own slot because it is the basis of the MAOI ‘cheese reaction’: normally MAO degrades dietary tyramine, but with an MAOI the tyramine load reaches the neuron and dumps a surge of NE → hypertensive crisis. Ephedrine, by contrast, is mixed — it releases NE and also stimulates α/β directly."
