      "x": "This closes the antifungal lecture — and with it the antimicrobial run of Lectures 19–24. The unifying thread is selective toxicity: every antifungal that works does so by targeting a fungal-specific feature (ergosterol, beta-glucan wall, or a fungal-only enzyme), exactly as the antibacterials targeted the bacterial wall and ribosome."
