      "x": "RSV, INTERFERONS, AND HPV. For RSV, ribavirin (aerosol) and especially palivizumab — a monoclonal antibody against the RSV F glycoprotein, given IM — prevent disease; originally for infants with bronchopulmonary dysplasia, now increasingly used in adults as RSV spreads. Interferons have antiviral, immunomodulatory, and antiproliferative actions across hepatitis B/C, Kaposi sarcoma, and other conditions. Imiquimod is an immune-response modifier (a TLR agonist that induces local interferon/cytokines) for HPV genital warts and some skin cancers — but Panavelil stressed it is a biological modifier, and that Gardasil 9 vaccination is the real HPV strategy."
